# Restart Policy

`spec.restartPolicy` ‚Äî what the **kubelet** does when a container exits. Pod-wide.

## The three policies

- **`Always`** *(default)* ‚Äî restart on any exit. **Long-running services.**
- **`OnFailure`** ‚Äî restart only on non-zero. **Batch that retries.**
- **`Never`** ‚Äî one shot, win or lose.

## Three subtleties

- **Restart ‚âÝ reschedule** ‚Äî same node, new process. A **node death** needs a controller; *a bare Pod won't survive it.*
- **CrashLoopBackOff** ‚Äî fast crashes ‚Üí kubelet backs off (10s‚Üí‚Ä¶‚Üí5 min). The **container** is `Waiting`, not a phase.
- **Jobs default to `OnFailure`.**

> `restartPolicy` heals a **crashed process** ‚Äî nothing for a **lost node**. That gap is why Deployments exist.
